div.p: The advance() method must handle the two-byte \r\n sequence as a single logical line break.

ul.li: Incorrect: Logic if char == '\n' or char == '\r': line++ results in a line-count of 3 for a single CRLF.
Correct: Logic if char == '\n': line++; col=1 ensures \r is treated as a horizontal advance (col++) which is immediately reset by the subsequent \n.
